sentences: Andrzej Trzaskowski was born in Krakow on 23 March 1933, the son of Stanisław Trzaskowski, a lawyer and music aficionado.
Andrzej began playing piano at the age of four; he was taught first by pianist Olga Axeull-Łapicka in 1940, then by Tadeusz Ciejka from 1941 to 1950.

Trzaskowski received his master's degree in 1957 after a thesis on the music of American jazz saxophonist Charlie Parker.
In 1956, Melomani performed at the Jazz Festival of Sopot, and Trzaskowski was recognized the same year as the best jazz pianist by a Przekrój poll.
From 1958, he played together with Jan Ptaszyn Wróblewski in the band Jazz Believers, which performed at the Jamboree music festival.
In 1959, Trzaskowski moved permanently to Warsaw, when he soon established his own band, The Wreckers, also composed of Alojzy Musiał, Wojciech Karolak, Roman Dyląg and Andrzej Dąbrowski.
The Wreckers debuted at Jamboree 1959.
